    <p>{`You have all your in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`SVG`}</inlineCode>{` icons inside an `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/assets`}</inlineCode>{` folder. The normal workflow will be to create one component for web and another for mobile, using some abstraction for each one like `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Icon.js`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Icon.native.js`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`But what if you can automate this process, so the only task you need to do is adding/removing icons from this `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`assets`}</inlineCode>{` folder. This is when generating icons becomes quite helpful!`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-tree"
      }}>{`assets/
  bus.svg
  train.svg
  flight.svg
  ferry.svg
  ‚Ä¶
** cast magic spell **
  # some idea of what the generated folder will look like here
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The generation of icon components occurs right before starting and building the application; this is to ensure that they are always up to date. The result will be a file which exports all the icons as React Components, each of which will call the proper implementation in the respective platform.`}</p>
    <p>{`At the same time, both platforms should implement the same API (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`propTypes`}</inlineCode>{`) making the icon system consistent and proving a better development experience.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "demo-time-"
    }}>{`Demo time üéâ`}</h2>
    <div {...{
      "className": "Image__Medium"
    }}>{`
  `}<img parentName="div" {...{
        "src": "/85d081df55f274b8a497cf70624e3e87/final-demo.gif",
        "alt": "Final Demo"
      }}></img>{`
  `}<figcaption parentName="div">{`Final Demo`}</figcaption>
    </div>
    <p>{`I created a repository from which I extracted the following snippets. If you want to skip the explanation and jump into the code, you can use this link:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/EmaSuriano/maintainable-icon-system-react.git",
          "target": "_blank",
          "rel": "noreferrer"
        }}>{`Repo link`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://emasuriano.github.io/maintainable-icon-system-react/index.html",
          "target": "_blank",
          "rel": "noreferrer"
        }}>{`Live web demo`}</a></li>
    </ul>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "time-to-code-"
    }}>{`Time to code üë®‚Äçüíª`}</h2>
    <div {...{
      "className": "Image__Small"
    }}>{`
  `}<img parentName="div" {...{
        "src": "/f56e072276e7ab00ad6f4dbf503693b1/lets-start.gif",
        "alt": "Let's start!"
      }}></img>{`
  `}<figcaption parentName="div">{`Let's start!`}</figcaption>
    </div>
    <p>{`So let‚Äôs start a clean project using `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`create-react-app`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`create-react-native-app`}</inlineCode>{`. After playing around a bit I realized that it‚Äôs easier to bootstrap the project using `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`create-react-native-app`}</inlineCode>{` and then add the missing files to the project.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
